{{Quote|Vaes Dothrak... the city of the horselords.|Ser Jorah Mormont|Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things}}
[[Image:Vaes Dothrak Title Sequence.jpg|right|200px|thumb|'''Vaes Dothrak''' as depicted in the title sequence, with [[Westeros]] in the distant background.]]

'''Vaes Dothrak''' is the only city in the [[Dothraki Sea]], located near the far northeastern edge of the region. It lies in the shadow of a single, vast peak known by the Dothraki as the [[Mother of Mountains]]. The entrance to Vaes Dothrak is marked by two large statues depicting a pair of stallions.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Vaes Dothrak is a place of peace where the [[Dothraki]] [[khalasar]]s may gather and meet to trade, but not to fight. Therefore it is forbidden to draw a sword while in the city, under penalty of death. However, the restriction is specifically on drawing a bladed weapon or shedding blood (which is considered sacrilege): should the need arise, it is permissible to kill someone in the city using other lethal means, i.e. strangulation or burning. Even so, due to the respect the Dothraki have for the city, violence within it is rare.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[A Golden Crown]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Dothraki holy women, known as ''[[dosh khaleen]]'', live in the city and are respected by all Dothraki.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/locations/vaes-dothrak/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 map, Vaes Dothrak entry]&lt;/ref&gt;

The city has a large marketplace, where foreign merchants from as far afield as the [[Free Cities]] and [[Asshai]] sell their wares.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[You Win or You Die]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
